WEBVTT

00:00:00.320 --> 00:00:55.400


00:00:58.647 --> 00:01:03.222
[Episode 10: Rudolph]

00:01:21.988 --> 00:01:23.654
Yeah.

00:01:23.654 --> 00:01:25.904
We just got to the hotel.

00:01:25.904 --> 00:01:27.188
Writer Kim!

00:01:27.188 --> 00:01:28.404
Yeah.

00:01:28.404 --> 00:01:31.071
We're at a pub, you should come.

00:01:31.071 --> 00:01:32.211
A pub?

00:01:32.211 --> 00:01:33.779
Yeah.

00:01:33.779 --> 00:01:36.404
It's not far from the hotel.

00:01:36.404 --> 00:01:38.022
Is that Writer Kim?

00:01:38.022 --> 00:01:40.313
Tell her to get over here.

00:01:40.313 --> 00:01:42.313
The Editor wants you here now.

00:01:42.313 --> 00:01:45.571
- Here's your chicken.
- Come with PD Shin.

00:01:45.571 --> 00:01:48.623
Sure, I'll check with him.

00:01:53.022 --> 00:01:54.446
Let's go.

00:01:54.446 --> 00:01:57.105
Drinks with Soon Rok, perfect chance to bond.

00:01:57.105 --> 00:01:58.230
Yes!

00:01:58.230 --> 00:02:00.688
Chicken time!

00:02:00.688 --> 00:02:02.324
They said chicken's waiting for us!

00:02:02.324 --> 00:02:05.072
The 4th floor, that's where your room is.

00:02:06.238 --> 00:02:08.063
The Editor said

00:02:08.063 --> 00:02:10.446
he's at a beer place and wants us to come...

00:02:10.446 --> 00:02:13.230
You heading there? Let me take you.

00:02:13.230 --> 00:02:14.647
What about you?

00:02:14.647 --> 00:02:17.946
I've got some work to do, so...

00:02:17.946 --> 00:02:20.821
Once you're settled, I'll take you there.

00:02:20.821 --> 00:02:23.772
- Chicken, chicken!
- Why bother going if Soon Rok's not coming?

00:02:24.772 --> 00:02:28.063
Wait, no chicken?

00:02:28.063 --> 00:02:29.654
I'm pretty tired too,

00:02:29.654 --> 00:02:31.397
so I think I'll just rest.

00:02:31.397 --> 00:02:32.398
Are you sure?

00:02:32.398 --> 00:02:34.188
Just let them know I'm turning in

00:02:34.188 --> 00:02:36.446
and I'll catch up with them tomorrow.

00:02:36.446 --> 00:02:38.280
Sure.

00:02:39.188 --> 00:02:42.272
You don't want chicken?

00:02:42.272 --> 00:02:45.655
I do want chicken, but...

00:02:58.613 --> 00:03:00.905
Going up.

00:03:01.605 --> 00:03:05.363
4th floor. Doors are closing.

00:03:05.363 --> 00:03:07.313
Which floor are you...

00:03:07.313 --> 00:03:09.322
I'm on the same floor as you.

00:03:10.354 --> 00:03:12.438
I'm rooming with the Editor.

00:03:12.438 --> 00:03:13.938
For real?

00:03:13.938 --> 00:03:16.529
That can't be fun.

00:03:16.529 --> 00:03:19.030
Such is life at the bottom.

00:03:28.654 --> 00:03:31.355
Silence again.

00:03:31.355 --> 00:03:32.855
Isn't it strange?

00:03:32.855 --> 00:03:36.272
A few days back, I couldn't stand it,

00:03:36.272 --> 00:03:39.655
yet here it is, feeling so sweet.

00:03:41.688 --> 00:03:42.738
Let's go.

00:03:42.738 --> 00:03:44.572
Oh, okay.

00:03:54.938 --> 00:03:57.946
Well then, good night.

00:03:57.946 --> 00:04:00.447
Yes, great work today.

00:04:35.355 --> 00:04:38.238
Sweet silence.

00:04:38.238 --> 00:04:41.022
I love how Soon Rok smells. What's his cologne?

00:04:41.022 --> 00:04:45.529
Does Soon Rok have natural curls?

00:04:45.529 --> 00:04:48.605
Soon Rok, ditch the glasses, get contacts!

00:04:48.605 --> 00:04:52.238
But it's Soon Rok's birthday.

00:04:57.238 --> 00:05:00.155
It's still his birthday.

00:05:11.904 --> 00:05:14.647
After being with him all day on his birthday,

00:05:14.647 --> 00:05:16.363
is it okay to just skip it?

00:05:16.363 --> 00:05:17.404
Yeah.

00:05:17.404 --> 00:05:19.071
There was cake earlier, remember?

00:05:19.071 --> 00:05:22.113
Please, that was Na Hui's cake.

00:05:25.154 --> 00:05:27.988
Wouldn't sending a gift now be too late?

00:05:27.988 --> 00:05:31.654
Staying quiet would look even stranger, no?

00:05:31.654 --> 00:05:33.946
Right.

00:05:33.946 --> 00:05:36.029
Yeah, skipping it entirely would be odder.

00:05:36.029 --> 00:05:38.779
It looks like he's still mad.

00:05:38.779 --> 00:05:42.113
Keep it light so he won't feel pressured.

00:05:45.071 --> 00:05:46.905
Okay.

00:05:50.154 --> 00:05:53.154
Too cheap?

00:05:53.154 --> 00:05:55.030
Then...

00:05:58.279 --> 00:06:01.113
Oh, this one's better.

00:06:01.113 --> 00:06:03.946
But with perfume,

00:06:03.946 --> 00:06:06.571
if it's not his taste, he won't use it, right?

00:06:06.571 --> 00:06:09.196
This is a bit much.

00:06:09.196 --> 00:06:11.022
No, not this one.

00:06:11.022 --> 00:06:13.363
Wait, he's not much

00:06:13.363 --> 00:06:15.321
of a drinker though, is he?

00:06:15.321 --> 00:06:16.988
Wait, or does he drink?

00:06:16.988 --> 00:06:20.246
I'm so bad at choosing gifts.

00:06:26.980 --> 00:06:29.488
[What gift are you looking for?]
Wait, only ten minutes left till midnight?

00:06:29.488 --> 00:06:31.071
Pick whatever.

00:06:31.071 --> 00:06:33.946
It's pointless if it's past twelve.

00:06:33.946 --> 00:06:36.154
What do I even pick?

00:06:36.154 --> 00:06:37.238
Fine,

00:06:37.238 --> 00:06:41.280
this works best. It's simple.
Let's go with simple.

00:06:48.904 --> 00:06:52.147
What if he's asleep
and you're just bothering him?

00:06:52.147 --> 00:06:56.363
Plus, isn't the Editor his roommate?

00:06:56.363 --> 00:07:00.454
What if the Editor spots it
and misreads the whole thing...

00:07:01.238 --> 00:07:03.696
Actually...

00:07:03.696 --> 00:07:06.030
that's not a good idea.

00:07:17.029 --> 00:07:19.413
What a nice breeze.

00:07:26.480 --> 00:07:27.904
- It's PD Shin!
- It's PD Shin!

00:07:27.904 --> 00:07:29.988
He hasn't gone to bed yet.

00:07:29.988 --> 00:07:31.654
And the Editor's nowhere around!

00:07:31.654 --> 00:07:33.488
Now's our chance!

00:07:33.488 --> 00:07:34.836
What time is it?

00:07:34.836 --> 00:07:37.488
Three minutes to go. It's 11:57.

00:07:37.488 --> 00:07:40.621
- Yumi, let's do it now!
- Yumi, let's do it now!

00:07:44.279 --> 00:07:48.105
Couldn't let it pass.

00:07:48.105 --> 00:07:50.155
Happy birthday.

00:07:51.863 --> 00:07:54.196
- Press it!
- Press it!

00:07:54.196 --> 00:07:56.155
Do it!

00:08:13.488 --> 00:08:15.530
- He's reading it now.
- He's reading it now.

00:08:24.938 --> 00:08:27.447
He's writing back.

00:08:30.196 --> 00:08:32.980
He's writing a really long reply!

00:08:32.980 --> 00:08:34.772
Hold on, he's erasing it?

00:08:34.772 --> 00:08:37.613
He must be thinking it over.

00:08:45.788 --> 00:08:48.088
Now he's writing it over.

00:09:05.063 --> 00:09:07.030
It came!

00:09:14.654 --> 00:09:16.404
What did he write?

00:09:16.404 --> 00:09:19.196
Thank you. I'll enjoy it.

00:09:19.196 --> 00:09:21.488
Have a good night.

00:09:22.696 --> 00:09:26.697
A smiley face!

00:09:29.613 --> 00:09:31.904
A smiley, everyone! Can you see it?

00:09:31.904 --> 00:09:33.488
- Yes, we can!
- Yes, we can!

00:09:33.488 --> 00:09:37.654
Nobody sends that to a person they hate.
Isn't that true?

00:09:37.654 --> 00:09:39.863
- Exactly!
- Exactly!

00:09:47.571 --> 00:09:51.605
A moon shaped like a smile
lit up the village that night.

00:09:51.605 --> 00:09:53.613
Unbelievable.

00:09:58.480 --> 00:10:00.563
This feeling is so nice.

00:10:01.438 --> 00:10:05.313
I forgot what this feeling was like.

00:10:05.904 --> 00:10:10.113
It's like my heart just melted.

00:10:49.529 --> 00:10:50.946
Editor.

00:10:50.946 --> 00:10:53.188
Oh, Writer Kim!

00:10:53.188 --> 00:10:54.654
You're up early?

00:10:54.654 --> 00:10:57.363
Yeah, have a seat.

00:10:59.105 --> 00:11:02.188
You didn't show up last night.

00:11:02.188 --> 00:11:05.113
I was completely wiped out yesterday.

00:11:05.113 --> 00:11:08.063
I seriously wanted to be there but no way...

00:11:08.063 --> 00:11:09.821
Smart move.

00:11:09.821 --> 00:11:11.238
You went hard

00:11:11.238 --> 00:11:12.363
last night, didn't you?

00:11:12.363 --> 00:11:15.154
No, I've really toned it down.

00:11:15.154 --> 00:11:18.230
I Da's been scolding me so much.

00:11:18.230 --> 00:11:19.988
She can be scary about that stuff.

00:11:19.988 --> 00:11:22.772
Oh, tell me about it.

00:11:22.772 --> 00:11:24.113
Would you like some coffee?

00:11:24.113 --> 00:11:26.404
Oh, yes, I'll have an iced Americano, too.

00:11:26.404 --> 00:11:28.322
- Yeah.
- Okay.

00:11:30.363 --> 00:11:33.579
What a beautiful day.

00:11:34.279 --> 00:11:35.779
By the way,

00:11:35.779 --> 00:11:38.321
were you out and about?

00:11:38.321 --> 00:11:41.196
- Excuse me?
- You look like you went out.

00:11:41.196 --> 00:11:44.904
No way, I literally just rolled out of bed.

00:11:46.196 --> 00:11:48.363
It's just, your whole...

00:11:48.363 --> 00:11:50.697
You're glowing.

00:11:54.990 --> 00:11:57.105
I told you not to do this!

00:11:57.105 --> 00:11:58.154
What's my crime here?

00:11:58.154 --> 00:12:01.279
The rule is to always look dead tired
around the editor!

00:12:01.279 --> 00:12:03.821
That's Writer 101, don't you know that?

00:12:03.821 --> 00:12:05.404
Looking at that glow,

00:12:05.404 --> 00:12:09.196
the writing must be coming along great.

00:12:09.196 --> 00:12:11.897
That's strange, not really though.

00:12:11.897 --> 00:12:14.446
Maybe I just got a really good night's rest.

00:12:14.446 --> 00:12:16.355
Busan water must agree with you.

00:12:16.355 --> 00:12:18.196
I even hit the sauna this morning.

00:12:18.196 --> 00:12:20.029
Can't you see the glow on me?

00:12:20.029 --> 00:12:22.272
You're practically shining!

00:12:22.272 --> 00:12:24.155
Gosh.

00:12:27.198 --> 00:12:30.446
By the way, I heard you shared

00:12:30.446 --> 00:12:31.904
a room with PD Shin.

00:12:31.904 --> 00:12:34.980
Right, well,
I tried but he said he's sleeping in.

00:12:34.980 --> 00:12:37.438
So no breakfast for him.

00:12:37.438 --> 00:12:41.404
That guy's secretly nocturnal.
He almost never does mornings.

00:12:41.404 --> 00:12:44.113
Is that so?

00:12:44.113 --> 00:12:45.246
Then, I'll go grab...

00:12:45.246 --> 00:12:47.154
Oh, right!

00:12:47.154 --> 00:12:49.946
You should try the sushi.

00:12:49.946 --> 00:12:51.738
Okay.

00:12:58.855 --> 00:13:02.259
Wasted a cute outfit for this.

00:13:02.259 --> 00:13:04.272
Since PD Shin's a no-show,

00:13:04.272 --> 00:13:07.905
let's stuff our faces.

00:13:09.696 --> 00:13:11.530
Writer Kim,

00:13:13.529 --> 00:13:15.738
did you sleep well?

00:13:19.946 --> 00:13:21.446
It's PD Shin!

00:13:21.446 --> 00:13:23.397
Good thing she dressed cute just in case.

00:13:23.397 --> 00:13:25.571
My gosh!

00:13:25.571 --> 00:13:27.613
Look at that messy hair!

00:13:27.613 --> 00:13:30.813
That T-shirt's so effortless. Nice taste.

00:13:30.813 --> 00:13:34.113
He literally just woke up.
Why is everyone losing it?

00:13:39.897 --> 00:13:42.572
Big sushi fan, Writer Kim?

00:13:43.696 --> 00:13:47.946
Oh, it's just because the editor said
the sushi here was great.

00:13:47.946 --> 00:13:49.196
I see.

00:13:49.196 --> 00:13:52.863
But I don't really like sushi.

00:14:07.196 --> 00:14:11.113
He's a sausage guy, huh.

00:14:11.113 --> 00:14:12.904
He likes chicken too?

00:14:12.904 --> 00:14:15.063
He doesn't eat vegetables.

00:14:15.063 --> 00:14:18.196
Total kid's taste buds.

00:14:18.196 --> 00:14:20.954
Even what he eats is adorable.

00:14:28.154 --> 00:14:30.530
How's the chicken?

00:14:36.029 --> 00:14:37.863
Have some.

00:14:40.522 --> 00:14:42.613
Even the short replies are cute.

00:14:42.613 --> 00:14:45.322
Why is he so adorable?

00:14:49.571 --> 00:14:50.938
- Got it?
- Yeah.

00:14:50.938 --> 00:14:52.822
Go get them.

00:15:00.363 --> 00:15:02.105
Where's he headed?

00:15:02.105 --> 00:15:03.980
Oh, to pick up some sandwiches.

00:15:03.980 --> 00:15:06.363
A few people didn't eat this morning.

00:15:06.363 --> 00:15:08.147
They'll all be up late,

00:15:08.147 --> 00:15:10.355
so it's free time until we eat lunch.

00:15:10.355 --> 00:15:12.238
Sure, sounds good.

00:15:13.863 --> 00:15:15.938
Any plans, Writer Kim?

00:15:15.938 --> 00:15:18.738
I might go for a little walk.

00:15:18.738 --> 00:15:20.688
Since I only arrived last night,

00:15:20.688 --> 00:15:22.480
I haven't really seen anything yet.

00:15:22.480 --> 00:15:23.522
That's a great idea.

00:15:23.522 --> 00:15:26.029
Make sure you soak up this ocean view.

00:15:26.029 --> 00:15:27.071
- Will do.
- Yeah.

00:15:27.071 --> 00:15:28.480
I'll be taking a nap.

00:15:28.480 --> 00:15:30.488
Sure, get some sleep.

00:15:49.272 --> 00:15:52.022
We lost him.

00:15:52.022 --> 00:15:55.072
He can't be far. Keep looking.

00:16:18.946 --> 00:16:21.405
There he is! PD Shin!

00:16:26.571 --> 00:16:28.529
There you are.

00:16:28.529 --> 00:16:30.113
Oh, Writer Kim.

00:16:30.113 --> 00:16:33.697
I figured I'd get coffee and take a walk.

00:16:34.730 --> 00:16:35.738
What would you like?

00:16:35.738 --> 00:16:37.196
- Let me...
- Don't worry about it.

00:16:37.196 --> 00:16:39.154
This is all for the writers.

00:16:39.154 --> 00:16:41.529
What would you like?

00:16:41.529 --> 00:16:43.863
Well, in that case...

00:16:43.863 --> 00:16:46.529
an Americano, not too strong.

00:16:46.529 --> 00:16:49.488
Can I add a weak Americano?

00:16:49.488 --> 00:16:53.288
Nice! That was so natural.

00:17:00.772 --> 00:17:02.613
That gift you sent me...

00:17:02.613 --> 00:17:06.738
- Oh, right.
- It turns out that cafe has the best view.

00:17:06.738 --> 00:17:09.022
Right over there.

00:17:09.022 --> 00:17:11.229
Before I leave for Seoul, I'll stop there.

00:17:11.229 --> 00:17:12.563
While we're at it,

00:17:12.563 --> 00:17:16.571
how about we go grab one together?

00:17:16.571 --> 00:17:18.071
Heading out for a walk, right?

00:17:18.071 --> 00:17:20.488
- Yes.
- Let me share a walking route.

00:17:20.488 --> 00:17:22.904
A really nice path came up last night.

00:17:22.904 --> 00:17:25.196
Are night walks your thing?

00:17:25.196 --> 00:17:26.363
Definitely.

00:17:26.363 --> 00:17:29.279
The beach at night is even better.

00:17:29.279 --> 00:17:31.488
Night beaches are my favorite.

00:17:31.488 --> 00:17:33.363
How about later tonight,

00:17:33.363 --> 00:17:36.029
the two of us take a stroll?

00:17:36.029 --> 00:17:37.821
Rudolph, your order!

00:17:37.821 --> 00:17:41.154
Rudolph, one cappuccino, one Americano,
and a ham cheese sandwich are up.

00:17:41.154 --> 00:17:42.913
They're ready.

00:17:44.738 --> 00:17:45.988
What?

00:17:45.988 --> 00:17:48.454
His nickname is Rudolph?

00:17:49.654 --> 00:17:51.863
Because his name is Soon Rok?

00:17:51.863 --> 00:17:54.488
Unbelievable. Rudolph?

00:17:54.488 --> 00:17:57.579
Such a cute nickname too!

00:18:08.404 --> 00:18:10.321
In the village that morning,

00:18:10.321 --> 00:18:13.496
a reindeer named Rudolph showed up.

00:18:18.446 --> 00:18:21.038
- Adorable!
- Adorable!

00:18:22.863 --> 00:18:26.938
Ridiculous, all of this.

00:18:26.938 --> 00:18:28.863
Yumi, get a grip!

00:18:28.863 --> 00:18:33.154
One emoji and you're like this at your age?

00:18:33.154 --> 00:18:35.538
Thank you.

00:18:37.279 --> 00:18:39.788
Oh, here, let me take that.

00:18:42.696 --> 00:18:45.071
By the way,

00:18:45.071 --> 00:18:47.461
when's your birthday?

00:18:47.461 --> 00:18:48.488
What?

00:18:48.488 --> 00:18:50.329
Your birthday...

00:18:52.105 --> 00:18:54.696
Oh, my birthday?

00:18:54.696 --> 00:18:56.196
Yes,

00:18:56.196 --> 00:18:58.196
your birthday, Writer Kim.

00:18:58.196 --> 00:19:00.404
Don't make it sound so formal...

00:19:00.404 --> 00:19:02.029
Regular birthday is fine.

00:19:02.029 --> 00:19:05.371
But still, there's a big age gap, right?

00:19:08.363 --> 00:19:10.246
So, Writer Kim,

00:19:11.363 --> 00:19:13.204
what's your age?

00:19:18.730 --> 00:19:21.273
[Episode 11: The Road to More Than Friends]

00:19:22.446 --> 00:19:25.022
Oh, my birthday?

00:19:25.022 --> 00:19:26.071
Yes,

00:19:26.071 --> 00:19:28.363
your birthday, Writer Kim.

00:19:28.363 --> 00:19:30.279
Don't make it sound so formal...

00:19:30.279 --> 00:19:32.154
Regular birthday is fine.

00:19:32.154 --> 00:19:35.496
But still, there's a big age gap, right?

00:19:39.113 --> 00:19:41.079
So, Writer Kim,

00:19:41.738 --> 00:19:43.663
what's your age?

00:19:47.480 --> 00:19:48.605
[Birthday]

00:19:48.605 --> 00:19:50.328
[Age]

00:19:53.605 --> 00:19:55.180
[Birthday, Age]

00:19:57.154 --> 00:19:59.196
Hey, you all heard that, right?

00:19:59.196 --> 00:20:01.738
He asked when her birthday is.

00:20:01.738 --> 00:20:04.904
And how old she is.

00:20:04.904 --> 00:20:06.238
Now do you see what's going on?

00:20:06.238 --> 00:20:08.529
What PD Shin actually thinks of Yumi?

00:20:08.529 --> 00:20:10.071
Romance? Yeah, right.

00:20:10.071 --> 00:20:13.363
It's standard when speaking to an older writer.

00:20:13.363 --> 00:20:15.446
Being polite means using formal words,

00:20:15.446 --> 00:20:17.613
and using them that way is only right.

00:20:17.613 --> 00:20:20.813
Besides, PD Shin's all
about keeping things professional.

00:20:20.813 --> 00:20:22.446
Give me a break!

00:20:22.446 --> 00:20:25.246
So you think it's fine?

00:20:27.904 --> 00:20:31.154
That's the first time I've heard age like that.

00:20:31.154 --> 00:20:33.913
It's not like I'm a grandma.

00:20:36.321 --> 00:20:39.446
I almost asked it plainly
but something felt off about that too...

00:20:39.446 --> 00:20:41.613
What exactly is wrong about that?

00:20:41.613 --> 00:20:44.363
The gap isn't even that big.

00:20:45.446 --> 00:20:48.538
What's your birth year, Writer Kim?

00:20:49.488 --> 00:20:52.613
Be bold. Just say how old you are.

00:20:56.988 --> 00:20:58.446
Take a guess.

00:20:58.446 --> 00:21:01.238
I believe you're...

00:21:01.238 --> 00:21:03.788
born in nineteen ninety...

00:21:04.404 --> 00:21:06.105
So this is where you are, PD Shin.

00:21:06.105 --> 00:21:07.714
Oh, Writer Kim.

00:21:09.738 --> 00:21:11.863
He's right over here.

00:21:13.821 --> 00:21:15.446
Saved by the bell,

00:21:15.446 --> 00:21:17.654
the age question went away.

00:21:17.654 --> 00:21:20.105
Not even able to say it? Forget it.

00:21:20.105 --> 00:21:23.279
Romance with zero confidence? No chance.

00:21:23.279 --> 00:21:25.397
Can someone please make him stop?

00:21:25.397 --> 00:21:27.380
He's such a buzzkill, honestly!

00:21:30.397 --> 00:21:33.238
I arrived so late last night,
I didn't see anyone. When did you arrive?

00:21:33.238 --> 00:21:34.654
Around eleven for me.

00:21:34.654 --> 00:21:36.321
- Okay.
- Did you sleep well?

00:21:36.321 --> 00:21:40.079
Not really, I was up drinking way too late.

00:21:41.654 --> 00:21:45.154
You know her, right? This is Writer Kim Yumi.

00:21:45.154 --> 00:21:47.238
Of course, I know her.

00:21:47.238 --> 00:21:48.404
Nice to meet you.

00:21:48.404 --> 00:21:49.563
Oh, hi.

00:21:49.563 --> 00:21:51.071
This is Writer Kim Ju Ho,

00:21:51.071 --> 00:21:52.779
who writes "Invincible Baseball."

00:21:52.779 --> 00:21:55.571
- Hello.
- Such a pleasure, really.

00:21:55.571 --> 00:21:58.363
Seeing you in photos is one thing,
but face to face,

00:21:58.363 --> 00:22:00.313
you're absolutely stunning.

00:22:00.313 --> 00:22:02.063
Oh, that's so kind.

00:22:02.063 --> 00:22:04.363
I really mean it, that's no empty line.

00:22:04.363 --> 00:22:07.522
I've been dying to meet you too.

00:22:07.522 --> 00:22:11.279
"Invincible Baseball" is crazy popular.

00:22:11.279 --> 00:22:13.863
That's ancient history, time to retire it.

00:22:13.863 --> 00:22:15.821
It's long past due for an ending,

00:22:15.821 --> 00:22:18.154
but bills don't pay themselves, so here I am.

00:22:18.154 --> 00:22:19.654
Would you like some coffee?

00:22:19.654 --> 00:22:21.154
Yeah, iced Americano for me.

00:22:21.154 --> 00:22:23.355
- There you are.
- Grabbing a coffee?

00:22:23.355 --> 00:22:24.404
I'm too full for that.

00:22:24.404 --> 00:22:26.272
One more won't hurt, come on...

00:22:26.272 --> 00:22:28.488
- Two iced Americanos.
- Sure.

00:22:29.821 --> 00:22:32.272
Oh, Writer Kim, this is Writer Kim Ju Ho...

00:22:32.272 --> 00:22:33.488
I already said hi, already did.

00:22:33.488 --> 00:22:35.488
- Oh, you did?
- Yeah.

00:22:39.529 --> 00:22:42.321
PD Shin handles this team, you know.

00:22:42.321 --> 00:22:43.446
Oh, I see.

00:22:43.446 --> 00:22:46.105
Yeah, you've been wearing PD Shin out,

00:22:46.105 --> 00:22:48.988
so I ended up taking him off her team.

00:22:48.988 --> 00:22:50.029
Oh, really?

00:22:50.029 --> 00:22:52.738
Yeah, you need to apologize for this.

00:22:52.738 --> 00:22:55.902
Writer Kim is already swamped
and you took her PD.

00:22:55.902 --> 00:22:56.946
Hold on...

00:22:56.946 --> 00:22:58.688
You can have him back.

00:22:58.688 --> 00:23:00.571
If you need him, just say the word.

00:23:00.571 --> 00:23:02.904
Your manuscript comes first.

00:23:02.904 --> 00:23:04.980
- Are you serious?
- Absolutely.

00:23:04.980 --> 00:23:05.989
Honestly,

00:23:05.989 --> 00:23:09.905
after all these years of writing,
I could do it in my sleep.

00:23:12.222 --> 00:23:15.904
- Bring him back!
- Bring him back!

00:23:15.904 --> 00:23:17.088
Then maybe...

00:23:17.088 --> 00:23:18.363
Writer Kim,

00:23:18.363 --> 00:23:19.821
don't buy a word of it.

00:23:19.821 --> 00:23:22.988
Without a deadline, he plays nice.

00:23:22.988 --> 00:23:24.238
But once deadline hits,

00:23:24.238 --> 00:23:27.980
he makes the biggest scene about his PD Shin.

00:23:27.980 --> 00:23:30.550
Seriously, really now,

00:23:30.550 --> 00:23:31.563
nailed it.

00:23:31.563 --> 00:23:33.738
Stop with that, please.

00:23:33.738 --> 00:23:36.113
- What's up with this guy?
- What's up with this guy?

00:23:40.696 --> 00:23:43.355
Honestly, PD Shin is the best.

00:23:43.355 --> 00:23:44.404
Thanks.

00:23:44.404 --> 00:23:47.779
Do you secretly dislike me?

00:23:47.779 --> 00:23:49.530
Here you go.

00:23:54.154 --> 00:23:55.730
His moods are all over the place,

00:23:55.730 --> 00:23:58.071
so it takes patience to put up with him.

00:23:58.071 --> 00:24:00.855
Come on, catering to anyone
isn't PD Shin's style.

00:24:00.855 --> 00:24:02.313
He stays in his own lane.

00:24:02.313 --> 00:24:03.813
Just keeps his head down and works.

00:24:03.813 --> 00:24:05.154
See for yourself.

00:24:05.154 --> 00:24:08.904
That right there is what makes him great.

00:24:08.904 --> 00:24:11.063
He's got real spine, that guy.

00:24:11.063 --> 00:24:12.355
- Editor.
- Yeah.

00:24:12.355 --> 00:24:14.488
Ten more minutes.
Everyone's waiting down in the lobby.

00:24:14.488 --> 00:24:15.696
Alright, got it.

00:24:15.696 --> 00:24:18.155
Ten minutes till we move out.

00:24:19.279 --> 00:24:22.768
Now it makes sense
why he's stone-faced on the job.

00:24:23.480 --> 00:24:26.197
I want to steal PD Shin back!

00:24:29.029 --> 00:24:31.821
Oh, by the way, Writer Kim...

00:24:31.821 --> 00:24:33.571
you said you went to the same university?

00:24:33.571 --> 00:24:34.946
Right?

00:24:34.946 --> 00:24:38.196
Yeah, that's right. Our years overlapped a bit.

00:24:38.196 --> 00:24:39.613
So surprisingly,

00:24:39.613 --> 00:24:41.676
you might be our age after all?

00:24:41.676 --> 00:24:44.480
Don't mind me asking,
what was your college year?

00:24:44.480 --> 00:24:45.480
Excuse me?

00:24:45.480 --> 00:24:47.355
Oh no.

00:24:47.355 --> 00:24:49.688
It was all going well, why that question?

00:24:49.688 --> 00:24:52.279
Change the subject! Change it now!

00:24:52.279 --> 00:24:55.357
I didn't even know we went to the same school.

00:24:55.357 --> 00:24:57.946
Only found out once I joined the publisher...

00:24:57.946 --> 00:25:01.730
Look at that bread, it's calling my name,
maybe grab some?

00:25:01.730 --> 00:25:06.730
I came back from the army
when she was just starting school,

00:25:06.730 --> 00:25:08.397
so there's three years between us.

00:25:08.397 --> 00:25:09.855
So that means

00:25:09.855 --> 00:25:11.863
you and I are only four years apart?

00:25:11.863 --> 00:25:13.771
That's right.

00:25:14.446 --> 00:25:17.790
For someone with such a baby face,
you're actually,

00:25:17.790 --> 00:25:18.938
quite a bit older than I guessed.

00:25:18.938 --> 00:25:21.571
- Oh, come on.
- What?

00:25:21.571 --> 00:25:25.322
Why don't the three of us be friends?

00:25:26.321 --> 00:25:27.571
Sorry?

00:25:27.571 --> 00:25:30.029
Four years apart
and he calls it friends? Please.

00:25:30.029 --> 00:25:32.113
Is he out of his mind?

00:25:32.113 --> 00:25:34.329
Forget that, check it out!

00:25:36.188 --> 00:25:40.530
He's literally doing the math on Yumi's age!

00:25:57.188 --> 00:26:00.446
The guy won't shut up.

00:26:00.446 --> 00:26:02.988
He's completely draining me.

00:26:02.988 --> 00:26:06.121
There's a real age gap here.

00:26:07.113 --> 00:26:09.621
True, that's a fact.

00:26:10.654 --> 00:26:13.079
Alright, fine, I'll own it.

00:26:15.272 --> 00:26:17.884
Is there even a chance here?

00:26:19.279 --> 00:26:22.988
Not even all my fingers could cover it.

00:26:27.654 --> 00:26:29.654
Don't fall asleep, Yumi!

00:26:29.654 --> 00:26:32.121
No time to sleep!

00:26:33.063 --> 00:26:35.613
What was the whole point of coming to Busan?

00:26:37.654 --> 00:26:40.522
Giving up now isn't an option.

00:26:40.522 --> 00:26:42.071
Love Cell.

00:26:42.071 --> 00:26:44.454
Didn't you know he's younger?

00:26:45.571 --> 00:26:47.613
Did you really not know?

00:26:48.446 --> 00:26:49.946
Our Yumi

00:26:49.946 --> 00:26:52.813
is way past the rookie stage.

00:26:52.813 --> 00:26:54.738
That's right, Yumi's the real deal!

00:26:54.738 --> 00:26:55.988
Sure, the years have added up,

00:26:55.988 --> 00:26:58.071
but that brings experience and wisdom.

00:26:58.071 --> 00:26:59.404
Plus...

00:26:59.404 --> 00:27:01.988
Her skin is flawless.

00:27:07.904 --> 00:27:10.772
Whatever happens between you and PD Shin today,

00:27:10.772 --> 00:27:12.272
it could be the start of something.

00:27:12.272 --> 00:27:14.571
- Yeah, no doubt.
- We've still got a shot!

00:27:14.571 --> 00:27:15.813
Be confident!

00:27:15.813 --> 00:27:17.404
Onward, to romance!

00:27:17.404 --> 00:27:20.163
- Onward, to romance!
- Onward, to romance!

00:27:23.022 --> 00:27:26.188
Should I text him after the meeting
and ask what he's doing?

00:27:43.779 --> 00:27:44.821
Hello?

00:27:44.821 --> 00:27:47.988
Hi, Writer Kim, it's Kim Ju Ho.

00:27:47.988 --> 00:27:49.621
Yes?

00:27:51.105 --> 00:27:52.154
Right, hi.

00:27:52.154 --> 00:27:54.654
What are you up to right now?

00:27:54.654 --> 00:27:56.371
Me?

00:27:57.779 --> 00:27:59.996
I'm not really doing anything.

00:28:01.196 --> 00:28:04.446
So here's the thing, lunch isn't until one,

00:28:04.446 --> 00:28:06.154
and we've got time to kill.

00:28:06.154 --> 00:28:07.446
I was thinking of swinging by

00:28:07.446 --> 00:28:10.279
Bosu-dong Book Street, kind of a work thing.

00:28:10.279 --> 00:28:11.821
Want to tag along?

00:28:11.821 --> 00:28:14.196
Bosu-dong Book Street?

00:28:14.196 --> 00:28:18.196
Yeah, a quick cab ride there and back,
timing's perfect.

00:28:18.196 --> 00:28:20.071
Come with me, just to look around.

00:28:20.071 --> 00:28:21.488
The place is packed with books.

00:28:21.488 --> 00:28:24.817
I guarantee you'll love it.

00:28:24.817 --> 00:28:27.321
I'm not sure, I don't really...

00:28:27.321 --> 00:28:28.654
Hey, PD Shin,

00:28:28.654 --> 00:28:31.313
two hours is enough
to look around and head back, right?

00:28:31.313 --> 00:28:34.071
Yeah, two hours works fine.

00:28:34.071 --> 00:28:35.279
- What?
- What?

00:28:35.279 --> 00:28:37.779
Soon Rok's going too?

00:28:37.779 --> 00:28:40.946
So if I'm going, who else is in?

00:28:40.946 --> 00:28:44.329
It'll just be me and PD Shin.

00:28:45.488 --> 00:28:49.313
Dae Yong's tied up with something, so he's out.

00:28:49.313 --> 00:28:51.821
All right.

00:28:51.821 --> 00:28:53.446
Let's go!

00:28:53.446 --> 00:28:55.154
Come on, just come with us.

00:28:55.154 --> 00:28:57.946
You might pick up
some inspiration for your writing.

00:28:57.946 --> 00:29:00.663
- Who's that on the phone?
- Writer Kim Yumi.

00:29:03.071 --> 00:29:05.654
Okay, sure,

00:29:05.654 --> 00:29:07.779
I guess I'll join you.

00:29:07.779 --> 00:29:10.196
I've got nothing going on,

00:29:10.196 --> 00:29:13.288
and I've been curious about Bosu-dong anyway.

00:29:15.563 --> 00:29:18.863
Perfect, meet you in the lobby in ten.

00:29:18.863 --> 00:29:20.496
Sounds good.

00:29:32.363 --> 00:29:33.654
Yes!

00:29:33.654 --> 00:29:35.404
We just keep running into each other naturally.

00:29:35.404 --> 00:29:38.029
Still, Writer Kim tagging along
is throwing me off.

00:29:38.029 --> 00:29:40.988
Having someone else around
actually keeps it casual.

00:29:40.988 --> 00:29:42.279
When you're in that more-than-friends zone,

00:29:42.279 --> 00:29:44.321
a third person is essential.

00:29:44.321 --> 00:29:46.029
Knew it!

00:29:46.029 --> 00:29:49.113
- Experience and wisdom!
- Experience and wisdom!

00:29:49.113 --> 00:29:50.738
PD Shin, we need to book a cab.

00:29:50.738 --> 00:29:53.079
Already on it, calling one now.

00:29:53.863 --> 00:29:55.297
- She said yes.
- No kidding?

00:29:56.563 --> 00:29:59.522
Hey, you're positive
Writer Yumi's single, right?

00:29:59.522 --> 00:30:03.863
Single, totally single.
She's my wife's best friend, I'd know.

00:30:03.863 --> 00:30:06.738
Okay, got it.

00:30:10.188 --> 00:30:11.321
Hang on a second.

00:30:11.321 --> 00:30:12.654
Hey, hang on to the cab.

00:30:12.654 --> 00:30:15.279
- What's up?
- I need to run up to my room for a second.

00:30:15.279 --> 00:30:18.822
- Good luck out there.
- Yeah, I'll see you later.

00:30:29.613 --> 00:30:31.863
Hi, PD Shin.

00:30:31.863 --> 00:30:33.821
Hey, Writer.

00:30:33.821 --> 00:30:35.904
- Where did Writer Kim go...
- He ran to grab his camera.

00:30:35.904 --> 00:30:37.905
He'll be right down.

00:30:40.404 --> 00:30:42.647
Hey, you're not wiped out?

00:30:42.647 --> 00:30:43.696
Sorry?

00:30:43.696 --> 00:30:46.863
You got in super late last night
and you've been going since early.

00:30:46.863 --> 00:30:49.946
If you're beat,
you really don't need to push yourself to come.

00:30:49.946 --> 00:30:52.196
No, really, I'm good.

00:30:52.196 --> 00:30:54.029
If you only said yes
because you felt bad saying no,

00:30:54.029 --> 00:30:56.113
I can smooth it over with Writer Kim.

00:30:56.113 --> 00:30:57.779
No, that's not it at all.

00:30:57.779 --> 00:31:00.654
I actually think it'll be good to check out.

00:31:00.654 --> 00:31:02.279
It might even work its way into my script.

00:31:02.279 --> 00:31:04.029
Oh, Busan?

00:31:04.029 --> 00:31:06.613
You're putting Busan in your story?

00:31:07.488 --> 00:31:11.154
Yeah, I think it's about to make an appearance.

00:31:11.154 --> 00:31:13.613
So what goes down in Busan?

00:31:15.654 --> 00:31:17.946
Still working it out.

00:31:17.946 --> 00:31:21.446
The female lead takes
a solo trip down to Busan...

00:31:21.446 --> 00:31:22.988
Wait, the female lead?

00:31:22.988 --> 00:31:25.829
The one who's scared of traveling?

00:31:27.446 --> 00:31:29.738
Could you lay off the questions?

00:31:29.738 --> 00:31:32.029
Why are you grilling me like this?

00:31:32.029 --> 00:31:34.654
Because I want more time with you, all right?

00:31:34.654 --> 00:31:38.030
Do I seriously have to say it out loud?

00:31:40.988 --> 00:31:44.188
Yeah, so anyway...

00:31:44.188 --> 00:31:46.897
Oh, the cab's here.

00:31:48.654 --> 00:31:51.113
Hey, PD Shin!

00:31:51.113 --> 00:31:53.863
Oh, hi Writer. You're here.

00:31:53.863 --> 00:31:56.613
- This is our ride?
- Yeah.

00:31:56.613 --> 00:31:58.196
Let's go.

00:31:58.196 --> 00:32:00.197
All right, let's go.

00:32:10.738 --> 00:32:14.863
Do you make it down to Busan often?

00:32:14.863 --> 00:32:16.029
Not really.

00:32:16.029 --> 00:32:20.488
I think this is only my third or fourth time.

00:32:20.488 --> 00:32:23.738
I was down here all the time as a kid.

00:32:23.738 --> 00:32:25.696
My hometown doesn't have a baseball team,

00:32:25.696 --> 00:32:27.571
so I grew up rooting for the Busan Cougars.

00:32:27.571 --> 00:32:28.613
Yeah.

00:32:28.613 --> 00:32:33.272
Man, I was baseball-crazy
but totally broke back then.

00:32:33.272 --> 00:32:34.730
Couldn't even swing a Tongil ticket.

00:32:34.730 --> 00:32:37.813
I was riding the Bidulgi all the way down.

00:32:37.813 --> 00:32:40.772
That Bidulgi ride must've taken half your life.

00:32:40.772 --> 00:32:41.821
Totally.

00:32:41.821 --> 00:32:46.113
But honestly, we'd just goof around
with the guys the whole ride.

00:32:48.613 --> 00:32:50.572
Knew it!

00:32:51.821 --> 00:32:54.821
- Sorry?
- I knew we were on the same wavelength.

00:32:54.821 --> 00:32:57.688
You know the Bidulgi.

00:32:57.688 --> 00:32:59.404
PD Shin's got no clue, right?

00:32:59.404 --> 00:33:01.196
You know what the Bidulgi train is?

00:33:01.196 --> 00:33:02.813
The Bidulgi train?

00:33:02.813 --> 00:33:04.855
No idea, right?

00:33:05.488 --> 00:33:07.496
Is it the name of a ship?

00:33:08.988 --> 00:33:10.188
See, what did I tell you?

00:33:10.188 --> 00:33:12.571
Their whole generation's got no clue.

00:33:12.571 --> 00:33:15.821
Seriously, we're the last ones
who actually rode the Bidulgi.

00:33:15.821 --> 00:33:17.696
I think it was what, around 2000?

00:33:17.696 --> 00:33:20.821
That's when they pulled the plug.

00:33:20.821 --> 00:33:22.947
See, we're on the same page.

00:33:24.821 --> 00:33:27.605
Come on, same team, right?

00:33:27.605 --> 00:33:29.530
Friends.

00:33:30.279 --> 00:33:32.488
The Bidulgi train?

00:33:32.488 --> 00:33:36.154
Seriously, we grew up in the same era.

00:33:36.154 --> 00:33:38.530
Not really, though.

00:33:39.446 --> 00:33:40.613
Gosh.

00:33:40.613 --> 00:33:42.813
That writer is seriously getting on my nerves.

00:33:42.813 --> 00:33:45.188
Why does he keep acting
like we're from the same generation?

00:33:45.188 --> 00:33:46.946
And right in front of Soon Rok of all people!

00:33:46.946 --> 00:33:48.529
We can't let this slide.

00:33:48.529 --> 00:33:51.446
Next time he pulls out some old reference,
let's just ignore it.

00:33:51.446 --> 00:33:53.196
Guys...

00:33:53.196 --> 00:33:54.904
we're in trouble.

00:33:54.904 --> 00:33:55.988
What's wrong?

00:33:55.988 --> 00:33:58.946
The place we just walked into

00:33:58.946 --> 00:34:02.206
is a nostalgia paradise.

00:34:09.487 --> 00:34:11.688
Here we are, Bosu-dong Book Street.

00:34:11.688 --> 00:34:14.863
[Jane Bookstore]
This shop's packed with books too.

00:34:20.605 --> 00:34:22.938
This place is incredible.

00:34:24.738 --> 00:34:28.204
Oh, old magazines.

00:34:29.321 --> 00:34:31.321
Oh, no way, it's Gukjjin Bread.

00:34:31.321 --> 00:34:32.863
Writer Kim.

00:34:32.863 --> 00:34:35.563
You remember this, right? Gukjjin Bread.

00:34:35.563 --> 00:34:38.147
I was obsessed
with Gukjjin Bread back in the day.

00:34:38.147 --> 00:34:39.196
You know this, right?

00:34:39.196 --> 00:34:42.404
We'd save the stickers
and throw out the bread?

00:34:42.404 --> 00:34:43.988
I remember.

00:34:43.988 --> 00:34:46.488
I must've bought a hundred
just for the stickers.

00:34:46.488 --> 00:34:49.230
And it was always
the same sticker every single time.

00:34:49.230 --> 00:34:52.238
Wait, PD Shin, do you even recognize this?

00:34:53.113 --> 00:34:56.530
Never seen it before.
Is this bread made by Kim Guk Jin or something?

00:34:58.488 --> 00:35:00.154
Made by Kim Guk Jin...

00:35:00.154 --> 00:35:02.397
See, what did I say, he has no idea.

00:35:02.397 --> 00:35:05.355
Their generation's
completely different from ours.

00:35:05.355 --> 00:35:07.105
Honestly,

00:35:07.105 --> 00:35:08.855
I don't know what it is either.

00:35:08.855 --> 00:35:11.654
What? There's no way you wouldn't know this.

00:35:11.654 --> 00:35:14.813
No, I really don't...

00:35:14.813 --> 00:35:17.654
Must've been before my time.

00:35:17.654 --> 00:35:19.529
Come on, we're the same generation.

00:35:19.529 --> 00:35:20.988
We're not, actually.

00:35:20.988 --> 00:35:23.488
We're really not.

00:35:25.113 --> 00:35:26.440
Come on.

00:35:26.440 --> 00:35:28.063
We're from the same era, right?

00:35:28.063 --> 00:35:29.980
Writer!

00:35:31.980 --> 00:35:33.813
Let's do a quick loop and get out of here.

00:35:33.813 --> 00:35:35.105
If we stay any longer,

00:35:35.105 --> 00:35:38.197
we'll never escape
this generation-bonding nightmare!

00:35:52.321 --> 00:35:55.821
This street is actually pretty great.
The atmosphere's lovely.

00:35:55.821 --> 00:36:00.322
How great would it be to come here
with just Soon Rok?

00:36:04.779 --> 00:36:07.238
Speaking of Soon Rok, where is he?

00:36:22.446 --> 00:36:25.063
You definitely know this one, right?

00:36:25.063 --> 00:36:26.696
[That Guy Was Cool]
Guiyeoni.

00:36:26.696 --> 00:36:28.779
They've got this book here.

00:36:28.779 --> 00:36:30.863
Honestly, Guiyeoni's

00:36:30.863 --> 00:36:34.404
practically a legend to writers like us.

00:36:34.404 --> 00:36:37.363
I don't really know much about that.

00:36:37.363 --> 00:36:39.279
Oh, stop pretending, no way you don't know.

00:36:39.279 --> 00:36:42.571
I'm telling you, we're different generations.

00:36:42.571 --> 00:36:45.772
By the way, where did PD Shin disappear to?

00:36:45.772 --> 00:36:47.697
I can't see him anywhere.

00:36:48.779 --> 00:36:51.488
He already took off.

00:36:51.488 --> 00:36:52.855
What? Where did...

00:36:52.855 --> 00:36:56.405
He had something to take care of,
so he left early.

00:36:57.529 --> 00:37:00.605
- But...
- I bet you're starving.

00:37:00.605 --> 00:37:04.822
Want to grab something quick
to eat around here?

00:37:25.294 --> 00:37:26.336
Hello?

00:37:26.336 --> 00:37:27.354
Where are you?

00:37:27.354 --> 00:37:29.071
I'm heading back to the hotel.

00:37:29.071 --> 00:37:30.279
All three of you?

00:37:30.279 --> 00:37:33.363
No, just me.

00:37:33.363 --> 00:37:34.821
Just you?

00:37:34.821 --> 00:37:37.779
He told me to go ahead.

00:37:37.779 --> 00:37:40.113
Unreal, that guy, I swear.

00:37:40.113 --> 00:37:42.030
All right.

00:38:08.779 --> 00:38:11.988
Hello, I Da.

00:38:11.988 --> 00:38:14.529
What's up?

00:38:14.529 --> 00:38:16.981
You resting okay? Having fun over there?

00:38:16.981 --> 00:38:19.804
Fun? I'm dead tired.

00:38:21.124 --> 00:38:24.113
You met this writer Kim Ju Ho, right?

00:38:24.113 --> 00:38:26.238
So, what's he like?

00:38:26.238 --> 00:38:27.327
What do you mean?

00:38:27.327 --> 00:38:30.738
My husband said the guy's a huge fan of yours.

00:38:30.738 --> 00:38:31.938
[Yumi]
Apparently he's been begging

00:38:31.938 --> 00:38:33.321
to be introduced to you for ages.

00:38:33.321 --> 00:38:35.522
- So you ran into him there, right?
- Yeah, I did.

00:38:35.522 --> 00:38:36.654
So what do you think?

00:38:36.654 --> 00:38:40.238
I've seen him around, he's funny,
seems like a really decent guy.

00:38:40.238 --> 00:38:42.154
Did you all plan this together or what?

00:38:42.154 --> 00:38:43.696
- What?
- You all teamed up

00:38:43.696 --> 00:38:46.446
to set me up with him, didn't you?

00:38:46.446 --> 00:38:48.988
He drags me along saying it's for research,

00:38:48.988 --> 00:38:52.238
and the next thing I know,
the PD vanishes without saying anything.

00:38:52.238 --> 00:38:53.438
- No way.
- So

00:38:53.438 --> 00:38:56.865
the two of us ended up having lunch
and coffee together. On our very first meeting.

00:38:56.865 --> 00:38:57.904
Like a date.

00:38:57.904 --> 00:38:59.818
Really?

00:38:59.818 --> 00:39:01.224
You did?

00:39:01.224 --> 00:39:02.313
Just the two of you alone?

00:39:02.313 --> 00:39:05.071
Why is everyone so desperate to pair me off?

00:39:05.071 --> 00:39:07.647
Oh, come on. That's not it at all.

00:39:07.647 --> 00:39:10.071
He makes good money,

00:39:10.071 --> 00:39:11.571
he's the right age,

00:39:11.571 --> 00:39:14.696
and you're both in the same line of work,
so you'd probably understand each other.

00:39:14.696 --> 00:39:17.488
That's the whole point.

00:39:17.488 --> 00:39:19.605
I see.

00:39:19.605 --> 00:39:21.446
Right age, sure...

00:39:21.446 --> 00:39:22.779
You guys click in a lot of ways.

00:39:22.779 --> 00:39:24.113
Oh, sweetie.

00:39:24.113 --> 00:39:26.613
So because we match up so well,

00:39:26.613 --> 00:39:28.613
the PD just conveniently disappeared.

00:39:28.613 --> 00:39:30.863
That was the whole setup.

00:39:30.863 --> 00:39:32.897
So, you don't like him?

00:39:32.897 --> 00:39:36.529
It's not that I don't like him.

00:39:36.529 --> 00:39:37.821
No.

00:39:37.821 --> 00:39:41.988
Who am I to say whether I like him or not?

00:39:41.988 --> 00:39:43.363
That's not it at all.

00:39:43.363 --> 00:39:45.464
Okay.

00:39:51.321 --> 00:39:54.363
Why did I even bother
coming all the way to Busan?

00:39:54.363 --> 00:39:56.488
This is unbelievable.

00:40:06.363 --> 00:40:07.904
Hi, PD Jang.

00:40:07.904 --> 00:40:10.946
Writer, I haven't seen you all day.

00:40:10.946 --> 00:40:13.154
I know, I've been pretty busy.

00:40:13.154 --> 00:40:14.529
Meet me down in the lobby.

00:40:14.529 --> 00:40:16.363
We're heading out for dinner soon.

00:40:16.363 --> 00:40:18.822
Okay, sure, I'll be right there.

00:40:26.821 --> 00:40:29.197
I should at least eat something.

00:40:40.154 --> 00:40:42.696
They spent the whole day together
and he just got in.

00:40:42.696 --> 00:40:45.238
Is this thing actually happening?

00:40:45.238 --> 00:40:47.154
Unbelievable, are they talking about me again?

00:40:47.154 --> 00:40:49.279
Come on, what's wrong with everyone?

00:40:49.279 --> 00:40:50.397
I'm telling you,

00:40:50.397 --> 00:40:53.613
he is absolutely giddy.

00:40:53.613 --> 00:40:55.405
Is that so?

00:41:00.029 --> 00:41:01.321
The nerve of him.

00:41:01.321 --> 00:41:02.696
Who does he think he is?

00:41:02.696 --> 00:41:03.946
But honestly,

00:41:03.946 --> 00:41:06.655
don't they seem like a pretty good match?

00:41:10.821 --> 00:41:12.529
Not really.

00:41:12.529 --> 00:41:13.613
What?

00:41:13.613 --> 00:41:15.404
I don't think they go together that well.

00:41:15.404 --> 00:41:16.480
Not a match?

00:41:16.480 --> 00:41:19.030
Why not? I think they'd be great.

00:41:28.147 --> 00:41:30.899
[Episode 12: Is There Any Chance?]

00:41:31.613 --> 00:41:33.363
I don't think they go together that well.

00:41:33.363 --> 00:41:34.571
Not a match?

00:41:34.571 --> 00:41:36.738
Why not? I think they'd be great.

00:41:36.738 --> 00:41:38.779
No,

00:41:38.779 --> 00:41:40.697
they're not a match.

00:41:46.488 --> 00:41:47.904
How so? In what way?

00:41:47.904 --> 00:41:50.405
Which part doesn't work?

00:41:53.321 --> 00:41:55.863
Editor.

00:41:56.904 --> 00:41:58.154
Oh, you made it back.

00:41:58.154 --> 00:41:59.654
- Gosh.
- You're here?

00:41:59.654 --> 00:42:00.904
How'd the fishing go?

00:42:00.904 --> 00:42:03.188
- Oh, Writer Kim.
- Oh, hi, PD Jang.

00:42:03.188 --> 00:42:05.480
You're impossible to find, I swear.

00:42:05.480 --> 00:42:09.071
I've been trying to find you everywhere.

00:42:09.071 --> 00:42:10.480
Let me introduce you.

00:42:10.480 --> 00:42:11.897
This is Writer Kim Yumi,

00:42:11.897 --> 00:42:13.688
and this is Writer Bae Woo Ju.

00:42:13.688 --> 00:42:15.446
- Oh, hi, nice to meet you.
- Pleasure to meet you.

00:42:15.446 --> 00:42:17.647
I'm a huge fan of your work.

00:42:17.647 --> 00:42:19.279
Thank you.

00:42:19.279 --> 00:42:21.029
Looks like everyone's already over there.

00:42:21.029 --> 00:42:22.238
- Let's go join them.
- Sure.

00:42:22.238 --> 00:42:23.488
- Okay.
- Let's go.

00:42:23.488 --> 00:42:24.571
Hi, everyone.

00:42:24.571 --> 00:42:26.446
Oh, you're here?

00:42:26.446 --> 00:42:27.696
This is Writer Bae Woo Ju.

00:42:27.696 --> 00:42:29.230
Go ahead and say hi.

00:42:29.230 --> 00:42:31.738
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you, too.

00:42:58.571 --> 00:43:00.071
This place is huge.

00:43:00.071 --> 00:43:01.988
Right this way.

00:43:03.772 --> 00:43:05.279
- What about the other team?
- They're all here.

00:43:05.279 --> 00:43:07.280
All right, great.

00:43:11.071 --> 00:43:12.863
Where's the restroom?

00:43:12.863 --> 00:43:15.029
One floor up.

00:43:15.029 --> 00:43:16.613
Thanks.

00:43:16.613 --> 00:43:18.655
Go on in.

00:43:28.571 --> 00:43:30.988
Coming to Busan was the right move, right?

00:43:30.988 --> 00:43:34.447
Absolutely, totally worth it.

00:43:35.363 --> 00:43:37.363
It was worth it.

00:43:40.904 --> 00:43:42.779
Oh, come on.

00:43:42.779 --> 00:43:45.367
Oh, Writer Kim!

00:43:46.613 --> 00:43:48.279
Writer, over here.

00:43:48.279 --> 00:43:50.363
Come sit right here.

00:43:51.113 --> 00:43:53.613
Hold on, that spot looks like a trap.

00:43:53.613 --> 00:43:54.897
Oh, Writer, come on over.

00:43:54.897 --> 00:43:57.238
There's a seat open right here.

00:43:58.113 --> 00:44:00.397
Careful, they're all around the same age!

00:44:00.397 --> 00:44:02.571
- Oh no, it's fine, I'll just...
- Come on.

00:44:02.571 --> 00:44:04.071
Go sit further in.

00:44:04.071 --> 00:44:07.397
This seat's by the door
and we need to come in and out.

00:44:07.397 --> 00:44:08.613
Over here.

00:44:08.613 --> 00:44:10.571
- Yeah, right here.
- Come over here.

00:44:10.571 --> 00:44:13.121
Yeah, over here.

00:44:15.946 --> 00:44:19.322
You made it.

00:44:22.113 --> 00:44:25.779
This spot's yours. I held it.

00:44:25.779 --> 00:44:28.446
It's the seat of honor.

00:44:28.446 --> 00:44:29.654
I appreciate it.

00:44:29.654 --> 00:44:31.615
It's nice to meet you, Writer Kim.

00:44:31.615 --> 00:44:32.654
Nice to meet you, too.

00:44:32.654 --> 00:44:35.105
I'm Isabelle.

00:44:35.105 --> 00:44:36.821
But something's off.

00:44:36.821 --> 00:44:40.196
You said it's the seat of honor.

00:44:40.196 --> 00:44:41.863
Honor seat? No way.

00:44:41.863 --> 00:44:43.446
More like the senior section.

00:44:43.446 --> 00:44:44.779
Oh, come on.

00:44:46.147 --> 00:44:47.571
Bingo!

00:44:47.571 --> 00:44:48.863
You sit here

00:44:48.863 --> 00:44:53.029
if the Bidulgi train rings a bell.

00:44:53.029 --> 00:44:56.113
That's such nonsense.

00:44:56.113 --> 00:44:58.688
Kids these days have no clue
what a Bidulgi train is?

00:44:58.688 --> 00:44:59.897
Not a single one.

00:44:59.897 --> 00:45:02.947
Besides us four, nobody's heard of it.

00:45:07.238 --> 00:45:08.738
I can't believe this.

00:45:08.738 --> 00:45:11.738
Here comes the old-timer talk again!

00:45:11.738 --> 00:45:14.204
Is that so?

00:45:16.063 --> 00:45:17.688
- Good work today.
- Please, don't mention it.

00:45:17.688 --> 00:45:20.230
You worked hard today.

00:45:20.230 --> 00:45:21.238
Let's toast.

00:45:21.238 --> 00:45:24.197
- Great job.
- Great job.

00:45:31.904 --> 00:45:33.613
Your attention, please...

00:45:33.613 --> 00:45:35.571
Let me just

00:45:35.571 --> 00:45:37.946
share a few thoughts.

00:45:37.946 --> 00:45:41.071
Our writers are always swamped,

00:45:41.071 --> 00:45:43.731
so this gathering's rare.

00:45:43.731 --> 00:45:47.147
I'm really moved today.

00:45:47.147 --> 00:45:49.071
Sure, plenty of you

00:45:49.071 --> 00:45:51.779
are old friends here,

00:45:51.779 --> 00:45:54.696
but some of you haven't met,

00:45:54.696 --> 00:45:56.821
even at the same publisher.

00:45:56.821 --> 00:45:58.238
That's why

00:45:58.238 --> 00:46:00.404
I want to do introductions.

00:46:00.404 --> 00:46:03.938
Now, where do I start?

00:46:03.938 --> 00:46:05.946
Hey, you know what,

00:46:05.946 --> 00:46:07.363
let's do it by class year.

00:46:07.363 --> 00:46:09.738
- Have a seat.
- Sure thing.

00:46:09.738 --> 00:46:10.946
Okay,

00:46:10.946 --> 00:46:13.863
so Writer Isabelle goes first.

00:46:15.196 --> 00:46:17.522
Here he goes again.

00:46:17.522 --> 00:46:19.113
- So annoying!
- By class year,

00:46:19.113 --> 00:46:22.147
Yumi comes fourth!

00:46:22.147 --> 00:46:24.613
Seriously, me again?

00:46:24.613 --> 00:46:26.904
Unless we're going by looks,
I shouldn't be first.

00:46:26.904 --> 00:46:29.946
Are we really doing pecking order here?

00:46:29.946 --> 00:46:31.738
Just go with the flow.

00:46:31.738 --> 00:46:34.617
Yeah, freestyle all the way.

00:46:34.617 --> 00:46:35.688
Freestyle?

00:46:35.688 --> 00:46:37.446
Let me start then.

00:46:37.446 --> 00:46:39.175
What?

00:46:39.988 --> 00:46:43.946
Hi, I'm Writer Kim Yumi.

00:46:43.946 --> 00:46:48.288
It's really nice to meet you all.

00:46:53.863 --> 00:46:56.780
You're so cool.

00:47:07.196 --> 00:47:09.696
So you're an only child?

00:47:09.696 --> 00:47:11.321
Yeah, only child.

00:47:11.321 --> 00:47:13.696
Five kids, I'm the last.

00:47:13.696 --> 00:47:15.904
I've got three sisters and a brother.

00:47:15.904 --> 00:47:18.654
Got it.

00:47:18.654 --> 00:47:21.154
So from a noodle company

00:47:21.154 --> 00:47:23.105
to writing? How?

00:47:23.105 --> 00:47:25.272
My degree's in creative writing,

00:47:25.272 --> 00:47:28.154
and that's pretty much my only skill.

00:47:28.154 --> 00:47:30.946
Finance team to writing,

00:47:30.946 --> 00:47:34.446
that's quite the jump, right?

00:47:34.446 --> 00:47:36.613
That's a long one.

00:47:36.613 --> 00:47:39.863
Not that interesting, really.

00:47:39.863 --> 00:47:41.855
- Hey, Writer Kim.
- Just, yeah...

00:47:41.855 --> 00:47:44.029
You remember that time, right?

00:47:44.029 --> 00:47:46.613
Back in Daehangno after the play,

00:47:46.613 --> 00:47:50.904
the three of us drank together,

00:47:50.904 --> 00:47:52.696
on the way to my place,

00:47:52.696 --> 00:47:53.855
you were on all fours...

00:47:53.855 --> 00:47:57.571
No chance. He's too far away.

00:47:57.571 --> 00:47:59.279
Today's a bust.

00:47:59.279 --> 00:48:00.897
Let's give up.

00:48:00.897 --> 00:48:01.946
Listen, guys,

00:48:01.946 --> 00:48:04.738
let's just hit the sack.

00:48:04.738 --> 00:48:07.788
Yumi's wiped out.

00:48:08.488 --> 00:48:10.488
- I walked on two.
- No, woof woof.

00:48:10.488 --> 00:48:12.897
- You went full dog.
- I wasn't that...

00:48:12.897 --> 00:48:14.029
Hang on.

00:48:14.029 --> 00:48:16.022
Where are you off to?

00:48:16.022 --> 00:48:18.238
Just to the restroom.

00:48:18.238 --> 00:48:21.579
You're taking your bag there?

00:48:23.455 --> 00:48:27.904
You sure keep a close eye on me.

00:48:27.904 --> 00:48:30.363
Oh, okay, go ahead.

00:48:33.855 --> 00:48:37.530
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

00:48:44.196 --> 00:48:46.197
Writer Kim.

00:48:47.446 --> 00:48:49.321
Where you going?

00:48:49.321 --> 00:48:51.738
Well...

00:48:51.738 --> 00:48:53.404
Mind if I slip away?

00:48:53.404 --> 00:48:55.484
Heading to the hotel?

00:48:55.484 --> 00:48:56.529
Yeah.

00:48:56.529 --> 00:48:58.404
I did my greetings,

00:48:58.404 --> 00:49:01.613
and all that running around wore me out.

00:49:01.613 --> 00:49:03.654
No problem, then.

00:49:03.654 --> 00:49:07.613
Round two's on, looks like a long night.

00:49:07.613 --> 00:49:08.738
I'll walk with...

00:49:08.738 --> 00:49:11.613
I'm good, it's just a short walk.

00:49:11.613 --> 00:49:12.904
Still, though.

00:49:12.904 --> 00:49:14.446
Really, no.

00:49:14.446 --> 00:49:16.988
You'd walk back alone.

00:49:16.988 --> 00:49:18.404
I want to walk.

00:49:18.404 --> 00:49:20.735
Have fun, okay?

00:49:22.904 --> 00:49:24.697
Head back in.

00:49:31.446 --> 00:49:35.196
So close, yet so far.

00:49:35.196 --> 00:49:37.488
It's tough.

00:49:37.488 --> 00:49:39.446
No chance to lock eyes.

00:49:39.446 --> 00:49:41.404
He won't even glance at her.

00:49:41.404 --> 00:49:43.738
Yumi's not on his radar.

00:49:43.738 --> 00:49:45.321
The guy's on the job.

00:49:45.321 --> 00:49:47.821
He's strict about work and personal stuff.

00:49:47.821 --> 00:49:50.113
Keeping it separate?

00:49:50.113 --> 00:49:53.654
If it's so separate, why obey Writer Ju Ho?

00:49:53.654 --> 00:49:55.779
He called them a bad fit, remember?

00:49:55.779 --> 00:49:58.279
It's the truth, that's why he said it.

00:49:58.279 --> 00:49:59.446
Don't you get PD Shin?

00:49:59.446 --> 00:50:02.529
The guy only states facts.

00:50:02.529 --> 00:50:05.071
Mind zipping it for once?

00:50:05.071 --> 00:50:06.946
Take it down a notch yourself.

00:50:06.946 --> 00:50:08.654
This crush is going nowhere.

00:50:08.654 --> 00:50:11.946
They won't even hit the flirting stage.

00:50:11.946 --> 00:50:13.586
Like you'd know anything!

00:50:13.586 --> 00:50:17.522
Romance is Yumi's genre.

00:50:17.522 --> 00:50:20.480
The romance playbook, remember?

00:50:20.480 --> 00:50:24.746
Without a hint from him, it stays a crush.

00:50:26.154 --> 00:50:27.446
Pay attention.

00:50:27.446 --> 00:50:30.904
[Crush, Sign, Flirting]
A sign from him in the crush stage,

00:50:30.904 --> 00:50:32.529
and it turns into flirting.

00:50:32.529 --> 00:50:34.196
No sign?

00:50:34.196 --> 00:50:36.321
It stays a crush forever.

00:50:36.321 --> 00:50:37.946
A sign?

00:50:37.946 --> 00:50:39.821
Yes, a sign.

00:50:39.821 --> 00:50:41.988
Look at Writer Ju Ho.

00:50:41.988 --> 00:50:45.071
If you're not hungry, maybe something cold?

00:50:45.071 --> 00:50:47.873
- How he acts alone with her.
- Nice and cold.

00:50:48.821 --> 00:50:49.863
Writer Kim!

00:50:49.863 --> 00:50:51.772
Always finding a way to sit close.

00:50:51.772 --> 00:50:52.821
Come sit over here!

00:50:52.821 --> 00:50:55.363
So you're an only child?

00:50:55.363 --> 00:50:57.547
Interest in Yumi, lots of questions.

00:50:58.488 --> 00:51:01.446
That's what a sign looks like.

00:51:01.446 --> 00:51:03.696
The kind of thing Writer Ju Ho pulls.

00:51:03.696 --> 00:51:06.113
Did PD Shin ever do anything like that?

00:51:06.113 --> 00:51:08.936
Tell me!

00:51:13.946 --> 00:51:17.113
How he acts alone with her.

00:51:17.113 --> 00:51:20.654
No, my seat is over there.

00:51:20.654 --> 00:51:23.404
They didn't have a seat next to yours.

00:51:23.404 --> 00:51:26.339
Always finding a way to sit close.

00:51:27.355 --> 00:51:28.980
Yes.

00:51:28.980 --> 00:51:30.022
Yes.

00:51:30.022 --> 00:51:31.061
Yes.

00:51:31.061 --> 00:51:32.105
Yes.

00:51:32.105 --> 00:51:33.203
Yes.

00:51:33.203 --> 00:51:35.280
Yeah.

00:51:35.988 --> 00:51:39.605
Interest in Yumi, lots of questions.

00:51:39.605 --> 00:51:42.113
Did PD Shin pull any of this?

00:51:42.113 --> 00:51:44.272
Tell me, has he?

00:51:44.272 --> 00:51:45.363
He hasn't.

00:51:45.363 --> 00:51:47.571
Zero times!

00:51:47.571 --> 00:51:48.946
Never has.

00:51:48.946 --> 00:51:54.063
It means PD Shin isn't into Yumi that way.

00:51:54.063 --> 00:51:56.946
He just stated the fact that they don't fit.

00:51:56.946 --> 00:51:59.613
Basically, no shot at flirting happens...

00:51:59.613 --> 00:52:01.947
Writer Kim.

00:52:06.938 --> 00:52:09.197
PD Shin.

00:52:11.779 --> 00:52:14.488
PD Jang said you left alone.

00:52:14.488 --> 00:52:16.738
She's worried.

00:52:17.404 --> 00:52:19.988
I'm already here.

00:52:19.988 --> 00:52:21.654
I know.

00:52:21.654 --> 00:52:23.863
I was too late coming to you, wasn't I?

00:52:25.029 --> 00:52:26.696
It's just around the corner.

00:52:26.696 --> 00:52:29.655
Still, it's nighttime.

00:52:31.696 --> 00:52:33.855
This is a sign.

00:52:33.855 --> 00:52:35.613
It isn't a sign.

00:52:35.613 --> 00:52:36.904
It is a sign!

00:52:36.904 --> 00:52:38.913
Ask him.

00:52:40.029 --> 00:52:42.779
You're making that up, aren't you?

00:52:42.779 --> 00:52:44.113
Looking for an escape,

00:52:44.113 --> 00:52:47.238
so you signed up to walk me?

00:52:47.988 --> 00:52:50.030
Well...

00:52:51.363 --> 00:52:53.947
You're not wrong.

00:52:55.904 --> 00:52:57.863
See?

00:53:00.154 --> 00:53:02.730
The writers there drink a lot.

00:53:02.730 --> 00:53:05.071
It's a bit much.

00:53:05.071 --> 00:53:06.488
I understand.

00:53:06.488 --> 00:53:08.279
It's overwhelming.

00:53:08.279 --> 00:53:10.030
Yeah.

00:53:12.477 --> 00:53:13.863
Let's go.

00:53:13.863 --> 00:53:15.628
Sure.

00:53:23.779 --> 00:53:26.130
- Going up.
- Get some rest.

00:53:27.404 --> 00:53:28.696
You're not coming up?

00:53:28.696 --> 00:53:31.154
Yeah, I can't sleep.

00:53:31.154 --> 00:53:33.154
Doing something?

00:53:33.154 --> 00:53:34.654
Maybe a film.

00:53:34.654 --> 00:53:36.571
A theater's just nearby.

00:53:36.571 --> 00:53:38.230
What's playing?

00:53:38.230 --> 00:53:39.813
It's Thomas Game.

00:53:39.813 --> 00:53:42.113
James King wrote the original,
so it's on my list.

00:53:42.113 --> 00:53:45.022
James King's a favorite of mine.

00:53:45.022 --> 00:53:46.063
Yeah.

00:53:46.063 --> 00:53:48.571
Crowds throw me off,

00:53:48.571 --> 00:53:51.113
so late runs work better for me.

00:53:51.113 --> 00:53:54.238
Turns out tonight's the final screening.

00:53:56.113 --> 00:53:57.904
Sleep well, then.

00:53:57.904 --> 00:53:59.696
Okay, enjoy the movie.

00:53:59.696 --> 00:54:01.446
Thanks.

00:54:01.446 --> 00:54:04.072
Doors closing.

00:54:12.063 --> 00:54:15.571
Isn't this actually a sign?

00:54:15.571 --> 00:54:18.230
All those movie details he shared.

00:54:18.230 --> 00:54:19.579
No need for that, right?

00:54:19.579 --> 00:54:21.571
Fair point.

00:54:21.571 --> 00:54:23.980
He's hinting she's welcome, right?

00:54:23.980 --> 00:54:25.605
Try asking to come, too.

00:54:25.605 --> 00:54:27.696
Yumi had it on her watch list, too.

00:54:27.696 --> 00:54:29.522
Won't he catch on?

00:54:29.522 --> 00:54:32.258
What if it isn't a sign?

00:54:32.258 --> 00:54:35.605
Hey! It isn't a sign!

00:54:35.605 --> 00:54:37.904
Cowards' advice doesn't count.

00:54:37.904 --> 00:54:40.488
Bravery matters when the moment strikes.

00:54:40.488 --> 00:54:44.738
If PD Shin gave a hint, reply to it.

00:55:05.300 --> 00:55:06.321
Hello?

00:55:06.321 --> 00:55:08.331
It's me.

00:55:08.331 --> 00:55:09.863
Yes, Writer Kim.

00:55:09.863 --> 00:55:13.113
Did you reach the theater?

00:55:13.113 --> 00:55:15.238
Heading there now.

00:55:16.654 --> 00:55:20.697
Once I got here, I couldn't sleep.

00:55:23.113 --> 00:55:24.980
That movie,

00:55:24.980 --> 00:55:28.322
I wanted to see it, too.

00:55:29.238 --> 00:55:31.488
Want to watch together?

00:55:48.404 --> 00:55:50.288
I prefer

00:55:51.404 --> 00:55:54.454
watching alone.

00:56:00.313 --> 00:56:01.922
It wasn't a sign!

00:56:01.922 --> 00:56:04.647
I knew it!

00:56:04.647 --> 00:56:06.313
Hey, you idiots!

00:56:06.313 --> 00:56:07.625
What did I say?

00:56:07.625 --> 00:56:10.905
Take it back! Just take it back now!

00:56:16.446 --> 00:56:18.571
Right?

00:56:18.571 --> 00:56:21.696
Movies are better solo.

00:56:21.696 --> 00:56:24.946
Honestly, going out's a hassle.

00:56:24.946 --> 00:56:27.897
I'd probably fall asleep anyway.

00:56:27.897 --> 00:56:29.363
Enjoy the movie.

00:56:29.363 --> 00:56:31.654
Recommend it if it's good.

00:56:31.654 --> 00:56:32.738
Okay.

00:56:32.738 --> 00:56:34.105
See you tomorrow.

00:56:34.105 --> 00:56:36.655
See you then.

00:56:41.988 --> 00:56:44.197
So embarrassing.

00:56:55.688 --> 00:56:58.571
You said it was a sign.

00:56:58.571 --> 00:57:00.647
Jumped the gun, I admit.

00:57:00.647 --> 00:57:03.522
Experience and wisdom, my foot.

00:57:03.522 --> 00:57:06.280
Keep barking up the wrong tree!

00:57:09.779 --> 00:57:12.488
I'm such a mess.

00:57:24.729 --> 00:57:27.738
How do relationships even start?

00:57:28.446 --> 00:57:31.829
Kim Yumi, you've lost your touch.

00:57:39.988 --> 00:57:41.855
What now?

00:57:41.855 --> 00:57:44.901
[Writer Kim Ju Ho]

00:58:10.938 --> 00:58:13.058
[Movie Tickets]

00:58:17.397 --> 00:58:19.245
[Writer Kim Ju Ho]

00:58:26.238 --> 00:58:27.279
Yes, Writer Kim.

00:58:27.279 --> 00:58:28.696
Hey, PD Shin.

00:58:28.696 --> 00:58:31.363
You left with Writer Kim, right?

00:58:33.154 --> 00:58:35.829
Yes, since it's dark...

00:58:36.904 --> 00:58:39.779
She's still up, right?

00:58:39.779 --> 00:58:42.071
But she isn't picking up.

00:58:42.071 --> 00:58:47.488
Bring Writer Kim and come here.

00:58:47.488 --> 00:58:48.822
- Sorry?
- Well...

00:58:48.822 --> 00:58:50.856
We're moving to a nice spot.

00:58:50.856 --> 00:58:53.154
You know the street stall by the beach?

00:58:53.154 --> 00:58:57.821
So, bring her here and hurry over.

00:58:57.821 --> 00:59:00.571
She doesn't handle liquor well.

00:59:00.571 --> 00:59:05.071
It's not about drinking, okay?

00:59:05.071 --> 00:59:06.571
Anyway,

00:59:06.571 --> 00:59:08.988
make sure she comes with you, all right?

00:59:08.988 --> 00:59:12.322
I'll text the address.

00:59:15.272 --> 00:59:19.363
Be sure to come with her.

00:59:19.363 --> 00:59:21.730
She can't come.

00:59:21.730 --> 00:59:22.870
What?

00:59:22.870 --> 00:59:23.946
How come?

00:59:23.946 --> 00:59:27.738
She said she'd watch a movie, so we came.

00:59:27.738 --> 00:59:30.613
It just started, so two more hours.

00:59:30.613 --> 00:59:31.904
What?

00:59:31.904 --> 00:59:32.980
What movie?

00:59:32.980 --> 00:59:35.488
So don't call her.

00:59:35.488 --> 00:59:37.697
She won't pick up.

00:59:39.696 --> 00:59:41.238
Yes.

00:59:41.238 --> 00:59:43.289
Yes, understood.

00:59:56.654 --> 00:59:58.363
That movie,

00:59:58.363 --> 01:00:01.621
I wanted to see it, too.

01:00:02.730 --> 01:00:05.030
Want to watch together?

01:00:15.488 --> 01:00:17.904
Please count me out.

01:00:17.904 --> 01:00:21.788
Just enjoy your drinks.

01:00:23.328 --> 01:00:24.949
Writer Kim.

01:00:24.949 --> 01:00:27.280
Still awake?

01:00:31.321 --> 01:00:33.529
Yeah.

01:00:33.529 --> 01:00:35.322
Why's that?

01:00:49.188 --> 01:00:52.447
Want to watch the movie together?

01:00:57.821 --> 01:01:00.730
That's a sign, right?

01:01:00.730 --> 01:01:02.780
Not a sign.

01:01:19.772 --> 01:01:23.105
You said solo's easier.

01:01:33.688 --> 01:01:39.542
[Want to watch the movie together?]
[You said solo's easier]

01:01:51.863 --> 01:01:54.697
Want to watch the movie together?

01:02:33.813 --> 01:02:35.148
It's still early stage.

01:02:35.148 --> 01:02:38.154
But if it keeps growing, it becomes love.

01:02:38.154 --> 01:02:40.696
- Hey, look behind!
- What?

01:02:40.696 --> 01:02:42.154
Am I your type?

01:02:42.154 --> 01:02:43.863
I'd like to pursue something serious with you.

01:02:43.863 --> 01:02:45.071
So sad.

01:02:45.071 --> 01:02:48.355
PD Shin gave me butterflies
for the first time in a long time...

01:02:48.355 --> 01:02:51.230
This isn't like PD Shin at all.

01:02:51.230 --> 01:02:53.480
What's with butting in?

01:02:53.480 --> 01:02:55.113
Writer Kim.

01:02:55.113 --> 01:02:56.446
You're amazing.

01:02:56.446 --> 01:02:58.188
If PD Shin accepts her feelings,

01:02:58.188 --> 01:03:01.072
the relationship begins.